The paper is about a large-scale dataset for object tracking, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The dataset is used for training and evaluating deep trackers, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The use of WordNet structure to guide class population and the introduction of the one-shot protocol for tracker evaluation also involve natural language processing and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The dataset contains video segments, which suggests that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses tracking algorithms, which may be related to robotics (cs.RO).
